The paper discusses a search technique that favors search results relevant to the user's current role. This falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA) for topical relevance, which is a common technique in Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of scoring documents, which is a common technique in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of geographic relevance, which could fall under the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) if the geographic relevance is related to location-based security measures.
